These are my Scenario Question 
First try solve it,Try Yourself 
ALL THE BEST


Objective 1 – Menu Items Analysis 
1. View all records from the menu_items table. 
2. Find the total number of items on the menu. 
3.Identify the least and most expensive items on the menu.
4. Count how many Italian dishes are available. 
5. Find the least and most expensive Italian dishes.
6. Count how many dishes are available in each category.
7. Calculate the average price of dishes within each category.

Objective 2 – Order Details Analysis
1. View all records from the order_details table.
2. Determine the date range of customer orders.
3. Find how many unique orders were placed within the date range.  
4. Count the total number of items ordered. 
5. Identify which orders had the highest number of items.
6. Count how many orders contained more than 12 items.

Objective 3 – Combined Insights (Menu + Orders) 
1. Join menu_items and order_details to create a combined dataset. 
2. Identify the least and most ordered items and their categories.
3. Determine the top 5 orders that spent the most money. 
4. View the category breakdown of items purchased in the highest-spend order. 
5. View category-wise breakdown for the top 5 highest-spend orders.
